- Abstract class cannot be instantiated
- Abstract classes are base classes
- A non-abstract class derived from an abstract class must include actual implementations of all inherited abstract methods and accessors.
- Abstract methods are implicitly virtual
- The abstract modifier indicates the incomplete implementation.
- Abstract classes can have both abstract and non-abstract methods
- Abstract classes are used for implementation in derived classes
- Interfaces are used to define the implementation
- Only abstract classes can have abstract methods
- Abstract methods do not have body, but only declaration
